INSERT INTO `wp_animalhealth_posts` VALUES (151,2,'2013-04-09 23:11:25','2013-04-09 23:11:25','<a href=\"http://www.anacapa-tech.net/animalhealth/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/biovetrex-logo.png\"><img src=\"http://www.anacapa-tech.net/animalhealth/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/biovetrex-logo.png\" alt=\"biovetrex logo\" width=\"498\" height=\"177\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-147\" /></a>\r\nAnacapa Technologies manufactures a phenomenal antiseptic solution called “Biovetrex” that has been proven to be remarkably effective at killing the most dangerous pathogenic bugs. \r\n\r\nBiovetrex inherits it’s basic composition to a Sodium Hypochloride solution which was originally called “Dakin’s solution” and was developed during WWI. It was highly effective in the treatment of battlefield wounds and was used extensively through the 1970’s.\r\n\r\nBut there were a couple  of the problems of Dakin’s solution. One, it had to be mixed on site and two, it only lasted for about a day. In the mid 1980’s a couple of doctors mistakenly determined that Dakin’s Solution was cytotoxic. These doctors recommended products that just irrigated the wound but did nothing to prevent infection, relying instead entirely on antibiotics.\r\n\r\nAbout 30 years ago, a class of antibiotic resistant strains of bugs began emerging: MRSA, VRE C-dif. just to name a few. More and more, these bugs could not be treated by traditional antibiotics. It was soon discovered that these new strains of bacteria were actually developing a biofilm - a sort of gelatinous material that prevented anything from penetrating it. \r\n\r\nThis biofilm allowed the bacteria to be 1,000 times more resistant to antimicrobials than a normal bacteria in suspension. \r\n\r\nOur product, Biovetrex, when applied directly to the wound bed, actually breaks down these biofilms. The Center for Disease Control agrees that “chlorine, chlorine compounds, Hypochloride solution  . . remove biofilms from surfaces and have a low incidence of toxicity” \r\n\r\nAt Anacapa, we also discovered a technology that gives our product a two year shelf life. It does not separate or breakdown over time. Anasept is proven to be safe and non toxic. AND - Anasept is approved by the FDA as an antimicrobial wound cleanser.\r\n\r\nWe have a wound cleanser - and a wound gel that is truly in a class by itself. what other product that has been out there for 100 years and yet there hasn’t been a single case reported of microbial resistance? NONE\r\n30 seconds to kill msra. 30 seconds to kill VRE. It’s phenomenal.\r\n\r\nThe Biovetrex solution has been tested in the most hostile environments simulating the actual wound environment. It wins every time. If you’re looking for an antimicrobial, a sporadical, a debriding agent as well as a deodorizer you’ve found it. Biovetrex is the finest antimicrobial in the world bar none. Nobody else can say that.\r\n','FAQ','','inherit','closed','open','','14-revision-v1','','','2013-04-09 23:11:25','2013-04-09 23:11:25','',14,'http://dev.adrianmillerdesign.com/anacapa//14-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0);
